Dialogs.Dialog: Rinko
So, um… What do you think of young girls…？
Huh. Well, sometimes I think they can be a bit sassy, but generally I like them. They're cute.
Sassy…？ I can see that.
When I play with my younger relatives, they sometimes say stuff you wouldn't expect a kid to say.
… Like？
What？ … Well, er…
… Hold on. I didn't mean that type of young girl.
What are you talking about？ Oh, geez. I got what you were talking about all wrong again, didn't I？
… I mean, I don't know.
You're convincing yourself of something taken way out of context. Don't do that. Now you've made it weird.
Rinko
When you're in a relationship, does the height difference between the two affect it at all…？
That came out of the blue.
I just know someone who was affected by it is why I'm asking.
Uh-huh.
When they walked side by side, they were very concerned about their small stature.
▲小早川＊▲, does it bother you that much？
This isn't about Rinko. It's about someone else I know.
I don't know why it bothers you. I don't care about it.
Well, I mean I observe the way you have to walk and all.
I guess I'm subconsciously trying to match your speed, ▲小早川＊▲. Am I doing too much…？
Together, then… I think we both are.
Well, I'd say you don't really have to worry about it.
Alright then… I guess I can tell my friend, then.
"Friend", yeah.
Yeah… my friend.
I guess I'm overthinking it, but are you still concerned about your height？
Rinko
It wasn't about me, it was someone I know.
Yeah, sure.
… It's true.
I can put it this way, when you fall in love with someone, those details really don't matter.
I wonder if that's the case.
Because most guys don't decide whether or not to go out with someone based on how tall the girl is.
Well, then. I'm a little relieved.
Make sure to tell your "friend" that, too.
… Well… It's just… You know… like when we're… kissing, you know…？
… Huh. I get it now. But I think it's adorable when I see you stand as tall as you can when you kiss me.
… you creep.
What？ How am I a creep for thinking that…？
You seem to be concerned about it a lot, but if you're short, you're also short…
Ouch！
Rinko
Don't keep tossing the word "short" at me.
… I was just saying that sometimes it's better to be short, don't you think？
How so…？
Well, it would be easier for me to carry this princess in my arms. … Oh, crap. Don't be angry.
I'm not angry.
Really？ What's the look all about, then？
I wonder what it's like to carry a princess in your arms. … Oh, don't get any ideas. Not now.
Would you be interested？
That's just because Rinko is a girl… But I don't think I want you to do it, though.
Oh, yeah？ Well, if you ever do want me to carry you like that, I'll do it whenever you want.
The thought is just so… embarrassing.
Well, if there's no one around to see us, why not？
Yeah. Then… Why is it that you've made Rinko curi-… You're such an idiot.
（You could just say that you want me to do it.）
Rinko
Random question. When you get married, do you want to go on a honeymoon？
… Heh. W-well, I, er…
Listen. It's about my dad… and my mom.
Hasn't he at least taken a trip since he remarried？
Nope. No honeymoon. Not even an overnight stay anywhere.
Busy with work？
That's part of it. But I think he doesn't want to leave his kids behind？
Aah. You're brother's still very little, isn't he？
Yeah. If it were just Rinko, I'd tell him he could just leave me home or whatever.
It's not a good idea for a girl to live alone, though. Even if for just a short time.
I mean one of us is… used to it. And then there's… well, you now, too.
… Eh？
Don't get any wild ideas. No one said anything about inviting you over when no one else is home.
If you can leave your brother with me, can you send your parents out to go on their honeymoon…？
Rinko
It wouldn't be that easy. Aside from my father… my mother has a tendency to worry.
Hmm…
What？ Ah, come on. Did I say something weird！？
I was thinking. I realized I'm calling her my 'mother' normally now.
… Don't be foolish. Your mother is your mother.
That's right. And Rinko won't be a child forever, either.
I'm glad that we're a real *family* now.
Look. If you keep talking like a parent, you're going to be old before you know it, okay？
Rinko
So I gethered up some pamphlets to see if there were any hot springs we could go to as a family.
Huh. You're starting to work on a lot of plans lately.
Well, sure. It's easy to make plans because it will be a one night and two day stay nearby.
Is it a couples-only mixed bathing spot…？
You keep thinking of the weirdest things！ Goodness！ You're such a perverted, filthy degenerate.
You're the one looking into hot springs！！ I was just trying to help！
So that's your reasoning…
Regardless, did you ever bring this up to your parents？
Not yet. I haven't found the opportunity to even start sprinkling an idea in…
It would be better to just talk about it as soon as you can. You can't make their plans for them.
Yeah, I know. Fine. I'll tell them when I get home today.
Rinko
… I got a call from home just now.
From home…？ What's going on with…？
Yeah… got me in a crying mess.
Why？
They saw Rinko going through travel brochures, so they thought I was hiding something from them.
At first, my mom was worried I was going to run away from home again… So I had to spoil everything.
That explains why you were crying on the phone…
Yeah. I was crying because her reaction made me happy…
You shouldn't have to cry. You're a good daughter who just wants to make her parents happy…
I see. Then shouldn't you try to get home sooner？
… Yes. So, my mom said… that we're getting together today to plan the trip out as a family.
Oh, that's great！
Yeah. I'll tell you all about it later.
You don't have worry about me. But now I want to go on a trip.
… Yeah. Thank you.
Rinko
I wonder where I'll be or what I'm doing in ten years…
I used to wonder that, too. It's been a while, but lately I've been thinking about my future again.
Could it be because of me？
Don't bee so vain. Then again… you did affect it a little.
▲小早川＊▲ ten years later…？ I wonder if you'll be an office worker, maybe？ I don't know.
What do you mean？
I mean, I don't think that's all you're capable of… that's what I mean.
I have no idea. But I have an idea of what you'll be: an old man.
… That's not true.
I mean your mentality. You're always taking care of others. You'll grow old before you know it.
… You're gonna be old, too.
What did you say？
Nothing.
How do you think you would see yourself in ten years, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Hmm… now that's a tough question.
Think about what you want to be in the future.
Maybe a fighter.
Wait… Seriously？
Of course not！ You would seriously believe that's what I want to be？
I've seen you play a lot of video games, especially the fighting variety. So I wouldn't be surprised.
Huh… You're one of those who can't tell the difference between reality and fantasy…
No, no, no. Don't start saying stuff like that. Geez. But seriously, what do you want to be？
… It's a secret.
Rinko
How about this. Instead of thinking of Rinko's future, what do you see yourself doing in ten years？
Me？ Huh… Maybe I'll be a businessman.
I wouldn't mind that. Do you have any other dreams？ If that's all, then this is why you're such a geezer.
Well, my biggest dream… If I could have a warm, loving family… I would be happy with that.
…Yeah, I can kinda see that.
Heh.
Are you crazy？ I used to think that getting married was out of the realm of possibility for me…
Because of your father's remarriage？
I guess there's that, too. But not only that… it's… it's good after all.
Ah, man. You're stopping when you're about to say something good again.
You're loud… and insensitive.
You still can't think of anything that you want to be in ten years？ C'mon！ Quit holding out on me.
Rinko
… your wife.
Hehe. Surprise！
What a joke.
I'm not even kidding. I'm sure you'll get married sooner or later.
That's right…
Are you jealous of your future husband？
… C'mon, man.
Heh. Good luck with that.
What was that？
Come on！
▲小早川＊▲, you got anything you've been super interested in recently？
Rinko
I've been watching a lot of cat videos online, I guess.
Heh. A lot, huh？
Yeah. I may or may not be watching them every day.
They've all got their own personalities, you know？ Some are stubborn, some are timid. They're all unique！
And when I see them, I just want to squeeeeeze～ them！
You really like your cats, huh ▲小早川＊▲？
Yeah, I have a problem. I have another one where… because of you I don't get enough sleep every day.
Yeah, yeah. Keep your video consumption in moderation, now.
Yes. I know, I know. I-it's not my fault I keep binge watching them！ It's got to be a sin to be that cute…
Got anything else from the internet that's interesting besides videos？
Rinko
… Eh, I don't know. It's my dad's computer, so I don't do much with it.
Oh, I don't play games online or anything.
It's far more enjoyable to beat up your opponent in an arcade.
Such arrogance and violence… all packed in such a sweet-looking girl…
When I'm playing a game, Rinko is not just a girl. No. She's a figher！
When we play against each other, it's all girl characters, though.
It's not satisfying to use a bulky mass of muscle to win. That's my policy.
Rinko
Oh！ Killer Bambies' unreleased tracks are now out online.
Is that what you've got in your music player now, ▲小早川＊▲？
That's right. This song is a live recording, so it's not mastered or anything. It's as rough as it's real.
Neat！ Speaking of which, have you ever seen them live, ▲小早川＊▲？
No. Killer Bambies won't come to Japan. They don't tour overseas.
That sucks. Just imagining ▲小早川＊▲ in a crowded concert hall is kind of funny…
What？ You think I'd get trampled at a concert…？ You don't think I would do fine in one？
I didn't say anything about that.
You wanna go to a concert together so I can be there to guard you？
Rinko
… Huh. Maybe it'll be okay for us to hold hands then…
Well, yeah. Of course.
それとさ……どうすれば背伸びるんだろ。
Alright then… Next. How do I grow taller？
… Er… You can drink milk？
You're serious about growing taller, huh？
When you ask it like that, you make Rinko sound desperate.
But you'd be happy with us being more relative in height, right？
It's… also… generally more of a balance with our walk speeds and stuff, you know？
▲小早川＊▲, I hope you know that I'm perfectly fine with the way you are.
Yeah… if you say so.
You don't have to force yourself to fit in with the others, ▲小早川＊▲. Just be yourself.
… Thank you. I think I can do that now.
